# Wizard UX Checklist

When asked to verify the wizard, check all of the following:

## Participants Step (Step 3)

- [ ] Adding a participant updates the counter and usage bar immediately (no refresh needed)
- [ ] Deleting a participant updates the counter and usage bar immediately
- [ ] Inline editing a name (click → type → Enter) shows the new name immediately
- [ ] Click target for editing a name covers the full row width, not just the text
- [ ] After adding a participant, focus returns to the input for rapid entry
- [ ] The participant list scrolls independently; counter + usage bar stay pinned at top
- [ ] The add input stays pinned at the bottom, always visible
- [ ] After adding a participant, the list auto-scrolls to show the new entry
- [ ] The "Next" button is disabled until at least one participant exists
- [ ] Group assignment uses a dropdown select (not inline badges)
- [ ] Dropdown has "כל הקבוצות" option that assigns to all / removes all
- [ ] Dropdown shows tooltip on hover: "לאילו קבוצות שייך המשתתף"
- [ ] Dropdown shows header text inside the menu matching the tooltip

## Groups Step (Step 2)

- [ ] Adding a group updates the counter and usage bar immediately
- [ ] Deleting a group updates the counter and usage bar immediately
- [ ] After adding a group, focus returns to the input for rapid entry
- [ ] The group list scrolls independently; type selector + counter stay pinned at top
- [ ] The add input stays pinned at the bottom, always visible
- [ ] After adding a group, the list auto-scrolls to show the new entry
- [ ] Changing a group color reflects immediately in the UI (color bar + dot)
- [ ] The color picker opens downward (not clipped by scroll container)
- [ ] The selected option card ring is not clipped
- [ ] "Next" button is disabled until groupType is "none" or at least one group exists
- [ ] If groups exist in the DB, groupType is always "custom" (DB overrides localStorage)
- [ ] New event with no choice: groups step is gray (not_started), NOT green

## Tasks Step (Step 4)

- [ ] Adding a task updates the counter and usage bar immediately
- [ ] Deleting a task actually removes it from the DB and the list (not just soft-delete)
- [ ] Inline editing a name (click → type → Enter) shows the new name immediately
- [ ] Click target for editing a name covers the full row width, not just the text
- [ ] Inline editing points shows the new value immediately
- [ ] After adding a task, focus returns to the name input for rapid entry
- [ ] The task list scrolls independently; counter + usage bar stay pinned at top
- [ ] The add input stays pinned at the bottom, always visible
- [ ] After adding a task, the list auto-scrolls to show the new entry
- [ ] The "Next" button is disabled until at least one task exists
- [ ] No "השבת/הפעל" toggle button exists on tasks
- [ ] Group assignment uses a dropdown select on the name row (next to delete button)
- [ ] Dropdown has "כל הקבוצות" default option that clears all specific assignments
- [ ] Dropdown shows tooltip on hover: "על אילו קבוצות חלה המשימה"
- [ ] Task limit uses a dropdown select on the name row (next to group select)
- [ ] Task limit dropdown has three options: ללא הגבלה / פעם אחת / מוגבל
- [ ] Task limit dropdown shows tooltip: "כמה פעמים כל משתתף יכול לבצע את המשימה"
- [ ] Each option in the limit dropdown has a description explaining its behavior
- [ ] "מוגבל" opens inline number input inside the dropdown (min 2)
- [ ] Selected limit mode shows correct color (purple/amber/cyan) and icon
- [ ] Changing limit saves immediately to DB (max_completions column)

## Shared: GroupSelectDropdown Component

- [ ] Dropdown trigger shows colored dots + label for selected groups
- [ ] Dropdown has header text explaining its purpose
- [ ] "כל הקבוצות" row with checkbox at the top
- [ ] Individual groups with colored dots and checkboxes
- [ ] Closes when clicking outside
- [ ] stopPropagation built-in (doesn't trigger parent click handlers)

## Wizard Navigation

- [ ] Refreshing the page returns to the same step (URL syncs to /events/:id/step/:n)
- [ ] The progress bar shows correct green/gray status for each step
- [ ] Groups step shows green when "no groups" was chosen OR groups exist
- [ ] New event: groups step is gray until the user makes a choice
- [ ] Nav buttons (Previous/Next) are always sticky at the bottom of the screen
- [ ] Step content scrolls independently between the header and nav buttons

## UsageBar (Free Plan)

- [ ] Shows "X מתוך Y" without warning text or color changes
- [ ] Updates when items are added or removed

## DB / RLS

- [ ] Actions table has DELETE RLS policy for owner (migration 013)
- [ ] Actions table has max_completions column (migration 014)
